<P>
   Some other useful small business Web sites with excellent links
to online resources are www.workingsolo.com, which also answers
startup questions and publishes a free monthly newsletter, and
Krislyn's Strictly Business Sites at
sites.krislyn.com/smallbiz.htm.
</P>
<P>
   If you like to do your own online hunting, two of my favorite
new search engines are Google (www.google.com) and LookSmart
(www.looksmart.com). The former, developed by Stanford graduate
students, uses sophisticated text-matching techniques to find pages
that are both important and relevant to your search so you don't
have to sift through so much junk. LookSmart of San Francisco has a
200-person editorial staff to cull and categorize the best sites.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &LR; Send small-business questions to entrepreneurs &LR; sfgate.com, or to
Peter Sinton, Grow a Business column, 901 Mission St., San
Francisco, CA 94103.
</P>
