<P>
   SPAIN-RESTAURANT (Roses, Spain) _ Some say it is the best
restaurant in Europe, possibly the world. No one mentioned that it
is so remote. A friend and I sped around hairpin curves on a
pitted, single lane mountain road, with nothing above us and the
Mediterranean a sharp descent below. The road snaked around the
mountain and eventually delivered us at the base of a sunny, narrow
cove. There was an empty beach, a rundown shack and a small villa
wedged into the hillside. This was El Bulli. This was the Michelin
three-star restaurant everyone was talking about. The one that six
top American chefs _ Charlie Trotter, Todd English, Norman Van
Aken, Roberto Donna, Jean Louis Palladin and Douglas Rodriguez _
would all flock to this same week and the next, not for an event
but on a pilgrimage. The one where the chef, Ferran Adria, is
rarely referred to as a chef, but as a mad scientist, a genius, a
Dali of the kitchen. By Amanda Hesser.
</P>
<P>
