<P>
   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   UT-BELLTOWER _ Reported essay on the reopening of the University
of Texas belltower, notorious for Charles Whitman's shootings.
We'll contrast the Whitman massacre of the '60s with Mark Barton's
of the '90s: Then it was seen as a bizarre anomoly; now we take it
for granted there will be more. This kicks off a continuing Atlanta
Journal-Constitution series on violence in life and entertainment:
Scared New World. (Hulbert, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 40. WITH
PHOTO ILLUSTRATION.
</P>
<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Q&AMP;A on the news, in two takes. (Bessonnette,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) (EDS: Moving on l (Lifestyle) and a
(General News) categories.)
</P>
<P>
   FASHION
</P>
<P>
