 CHRON  
These are the stories The San Francisco Chronicle Food section
plans to move Wednesday, September 15, on the New York Times wire.
Questions? Please call Lesli Neilson at 415-777-8402. &HT;     SAN FRANCISCO _  THE BEST WAY  _ In our new ``Best Way'' column
starting today, the Food staff will systematically challenge many
of cooking truisms and techniques that our mothers, friends and
cookbook authors have taught us. We'll examine preparation
presumptions and try to establish the most reliable way to cook
many of our favorite foods. &HT;    In this week's column we present our findings on the best way to
bake a potato and whether or not to marinate poultry and pork
before cooking.
 &HT;     Introduction by Michael Bauer  
 By Elizabeth Brubaker  
 By Stephen Baker  
 c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; WORKING &LR;  _ Bay Area grocery stores are making it
possible for us to cook quickly without having to resort to frozen
or heavily processed foods. With all products like fresh salsa,
