<P>
   SCI-VT-STARGAZERS (Springfield, Vt.) _ Amateur astronomers who
cherish Vermont's dark night skies suffered a blow this week when
residents of this economically depressed town voted to allow
construction of a prison nearby. Astronomy enthusiasts fear that
the 350-bed prison's glaring lights will spoil viewing at Breezy
Hill 3.8 miles away _ one of New England's main star-gazing
centers. By Malcolm W. Browne.
</P>
