   CIR-COMPUTER-REBATES (Undated) _ Faced with falling prices and a
stream of new products that threaten the already brief shelf lives
of existing ones, manufacturers and retailers of computers,
peripherals and software are relying more and more on rebates to
attract customers. And for more and more customers, the experience
of redeeming the rebate is not a pleasant one. By Catherine
Greenman.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   CIR-VISOR (Undated) _ The newest handheld device, the Visor, an
all-in-one organizer/everything, that looks like a cross between a
game boy and a palm pilot, was announced Tuesday. It has been
eagerly anticipated by techies, largely because it comes from the
people who invented the Palm Pilot. Here's a look at the people who
founded Handspring, and how and why they decided to gamble that
consumers really want an all-in-one device. By Katie Hafner.
</P>
