billionaire. But it's not only the money. He bubbles with zeal to
bring the world ``open-platform, programmable switches'' and likes
having the global platform of Lucent to do it. By Peter Howe. 1400
words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   MCDONALDS-MAKEOVER (Undated) _ For the first 30 years of its
history, McDonald's ruled fast food. But as competition
intensifies, the chain is undergoing a subtle -- and expensive
--middle-age makeover. By Chris Reidy. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   MEDIA-CABAL (Undated) _ Some people see the CBS-Viacom deal as a
triumph for master dealmaker Sumner Redstone. Others are horrified
at the prospect of Redstone joining a media cabal including Rupert
Murdoch, Michael Eisner, and Gerry Levin. By Peter Howe. 1800
words.
</P>
<P>
   ONBUSINESS-COLUMN (Undated) _ Proxy analysts recommend voting
against Harcourt General's planned spinoff of Neiman Marcus Group.
By Steven Syre and Charles Stein.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   GLF-RYDER-OLAZABAL (Brookline, Mass.) _ This has been a
breakthrough year for Jose Maria Olazabal, but he knows it could
have been much better if he hadn't carried the concept to such
literal extremes. By Bob Duffy. 850 words.
</P>
<P>
   BOX-TRINIDAD (Cupey Alto, Puerto Rico) _ Felix Trinidad fights
the WBC champion Friday to unify the welterweight title. The match
pits perhaps the two best fighters in the world, a fire raging
inside each like flames licking up dry timber. By Ron Borges. (2
takes)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-MCDONOUGH-COLUMN (Undated) _ Drew Bledsoe is ``as good as
anyone in the league right now,'' says the Indianapolis Colts head
coach. By Will McDonough. 1000 words.
</P>
