<P>
   With photos.
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS-TOWER (Austin, Texas) _ There are two buildings that lord
over this city: the state capitol and the University of Texas
Tower. But if, as University of Texas officials say, the Tower
symbolizes the school's heart and its aspirations, it is also
tainted by tragedy _ one the University hopes will finally end
Wednesday, when the Tower reopened for the first time in 25 years.
By Jim Yardley.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   FINANCIAL
</P>
<P>
   (Will move in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   AUTO-TALKS (Detroit) _ The auto industry's three-year labor
contracts covering nearly 400,000 factory workers expired at
midnight Tuesday. They could settle, strike or do nothing Wednesday
night. By Robyn Meredith.
</P>
</TEXT>
