<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Sept. 16 and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, contact Susan Leh at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   TWENTIETH-CENTURY (Los Angeles) _ 20th Century Insurance
announced it is re-entering the homeowner insurance market, 5{
years after claims from the Northridge Earthquake nearly wiped out
the Woodland Hills-based insurer. By Gregory Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   FIELDS-AIRCRAFT (Simi Valley) _ Fields Aircraft Spares Inc. has
hit some turbulence. The Simi Valley-based company that customizes
airplane cabins, will cut its staff nearly in half _ to 126
employees _ and reduce executive compensation by about 20 percent
in the face of a bad quarterly report and dim prospects for the
near future. By Dave McNary.
</P>
