<HEADLINE>
TEST YOUR LITERARY KNOWLEDGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   There have been color-coded quizzes previously, and some titles
are recycled here, but this one's entirely different. It's a
fill-in-the-blank exercise, in which you know or guess the
appropriate hue that completes the title. You pass this one with
seven correct answers, and 10 right will get you an A. Answers are
on the opposite page.
</P>
<P>
   The titles:
</P>
<P>
   1. ``______ Mansions'' by W.H. Hudson
</P>
<P>
   2. ``______ Voyage'' by Conrad Aiken
</P>
<P>
   3. ``The ______ Jacket'' by George Hazelton and Harry Bonvino
</P>
<P>
   4. ``______ April'' by Julia Peterkin
</P>
<P>
   5. ``All the ______ Twilights'' by Miriam Scattone
</P>
<P>
   6. ``______ Shod'' by Newton Fuessle
</P>
<P>
   7. ``The ______ Champion'' by Nathaniel Hawthorne
</P>
<P>
   8. ``A Study in ______ '' by Arthur Conan Doyle
</P>
<P>
   9. ``The Woman in ______'' by Wilkie Collins
</P>
<P>
   10. ``The Burnt ______ Heresy'' by Charles Willeford
</P>
<P>
   11. ``The Color ______ '' by Alice Walker
</P>
<P>
   12. ``The ______ Pony'' by John Steinbeck
</P>
<P>
   13. ``______ on ______ '' by Tess Slesinger
</P>
<P>
   14. ``The _____ and the ______ '' by Stendhal
</P>
<P>
   The color options: a. black; b. blue; c. brown; d. gold; e.
green; f. grey; g. orange; h. purple; i. red; j. scarlet; k. white;
l. yellow
</P>
<P>
   Quiz answers: 1-e; 2-b; 3-l; 4-a; 5-c; 6-d; 7-f; 8-j; 9-k; 10-g;
11-h; 12-i; 13-k and a; 14-i and a.
</P>
