<P>
   BELMONT-BOARD (Los Angeles) _ A day after the Mullinax Report
charged the LAUSD with widespread incompetence and wrongdoing in
the Belmont Learning Center scandal, the school board scrambled to
map out a strategy, sought private legal advice and considered
excluding Superintendent Ruben Zacarias from talks. By Greg
Gittrich. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national
news file.)
</P>
<P>
   ALLERGY-ATTACKS (Los Angeles) _ Allergy sufferers have wheezed
through an especially bad summer, as unusually moist weather kept
mold and pollen in the air. But the worst is yet to come _ the late
summer allergy season is in full bloom. And the problem is
especially dangerous in Los Angeles, the worst area in the country
for asthma, according to the Washington, D.C.,-based Asthma in
America. By Steve Carney. (Will move in the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news file.)
</P>
<P>
   INTERNATIONAL-CRICKET (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles' San Fernando
Valley is the first place in the United States to host an
international cricket match that is broadcast on television. More
than half a billion people worldwide are expected to tune in their
TVs for one of the most anticipated sporting events of the year _
the USA Cricket Association's international cricket matches. By
Phillip Browne. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a''
national news file.)
</P>
<P>
   TWENTIETH-CENTURY (Los Angeles) _ 20th Century Insurance
announced it is re-entering the homeowner insurance market, 5{
years after claims from the Northridge Earthquake nearly wiped out
the Woodland Hills-based insurer. By Gregory Wilcox. (Will move in
the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   FIELDS-AIRCRAFT (Simi Valley) _ Fields Aircraft Spares Inc. has
hit some turbulence. The Simi Valley-based company that customizes
airplane cabins, will cut its staff nearly in half _ to 126
employees _ and reduce executive compensation by about 20 percent
in the face of a bad quarterly report and dim prospects for the
near future. By Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news
file.)
</P>
