controversial piece of his bill to reform the campaign finance
system in the hopes of finally breaking the filibuster that has
prevented the measure from passing for years, the ``Arizona
Republic'' has learned. When the bill is unveiled Thursday, it will
not include a provision subjecting interest groups to federal
campaign-finance limits and disclosure requirements when they
broadcast political advertisements near elections. That provision
was ardently opposed by anti-abortion groups and the National Rifle
Association, among others during the House debate earlier this week
