<SLUG> BC-BROWN-SEX-TEXAS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
STATE SENATOR, 57, APOLOGIZES FOR GROPING COLLEGE STUDENT 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By STEVE OLAFSON 
c.1999 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANGLETON, Texas _ State Sen. J.E. ``Buster'' Brown, the ranking
Republican in the Texas Senate, apologized Wednesday for making
unwanted sexual advances toward a former employee.
</P>
<P>
   The woman, a 20-year-old college student, had complained that
the longtime legislator groped her in his office.
</P>
<P>
   Angleton is about 35 miles south of downtown Houston.
</P>
<P>
   The apology averts any criminal prosecution of the senator for
the incident, but Lake Jackson police said Wednesday they will
investigate a complaint from another woman who is making similar
allegations against the senator.
</P>
<P>
   Brown, 57, apologized to his former employee, Tiffany Black, in
a face-to-face meeting Wednesday morning in an Angleton park, where
he read her a one-page written apology.
</P>
<P>
   ``Dear Ms. Black: I am sorry for making unwanted sexual advances
towards you,'' the senator's apology stated. ``You have been a good
employee and I should not have placed you in this situation. This
is my responsibility and I will seek any necessary corrective
measures, including counseling. I have not been forced or pressured
in any way to make this apology. I am doing this because it is the
right thing to do. Please accept this sincere apology.
</P>
<P>
   Sincerely,
</P>
<P>
   James E. (Buster) Brown.''
</P>
<P>
   Brown handed the written apology to Black during the brief
meeting, which was attended by Brown's wife, Jill, Black's fiancee
and Black's mother, Renee Atmar, said Brazoria County District
Attorney Jeri Yenne, who also was there. She said Brown and Black
had agreed the park would be acceptable for the meeting.
</P>
<P>
   Yenne said no further action will be taken against Brown in
connection with Black's allegations.
</P>
<P>
   Had Brown not apologized, Yenne said she ``probably'' would have
reviewed the case for possible prosecution as a Class C misdemeanor
assault.
</P>
<P>
   Black, a Brazosport College student who had worked for Brown
about a year, told police that Brown tried to kiss her and touched
her breasts and buttocks while he was giving her a golf lesson in
his Lake Jackson office Sept. 2.
</P>
<P>
   She resigned the same day and complained to Lake Jackson police.
</P>
<P>
   Black was unavailable to comment on Brown's apology, but Yenne,
the district attorney, said the apology was important to the young
woman.
</P>
<P>
   ``It provided some validation to her complaint,'' she said.
``We're all human and I have victims tell me all the time that the
one thing that bothered them is they never got an apology.``
</P>
<P>
   Yenne said Brown's apology perhaps opens the senator to
liabililty in a civil lawsuit and that Black and her mother realize
that is a legal option.
</P>
<P>
   Neither Brown nor his lawyer, Michael Phillips of Angleton,
could be reached for comment.
</P>
<P>
   Lake Jackson Police Chief Paul Hromadka, meanwhile, said police
have received a call from an Alvin woman who claims Brown made
similar unwanted sexual advances toward her.
</P>
<P>
   Police planned to interview the woman Wednesday night, Hromadka
said.
</P>
<P>
   ``We will investigate any and all allegations if it occurred in
our jurisdiction and within the statute of limitations,'' Hromadka
said.
</P>
<P>
   Misdemeanor cases must be presented to a grand jury within two
years of the incident, Hromadka said.
</P>
<P>
   ``We don't know how long ago this may have occurred,'' he said
of the latest allegations against Brown.
</P>
<P>
   Brown, a Lake Jackson lawyer, has been mentioned as a possible
candidate for lieutenant governor should Gov. George W. Bush be
elected president and be succeeded by Lt. Gov. Rick Perry.
</P>
<P>
   Brown, who has run unsuccessfully for attorney general, has
represented District 17 since 1981. The district encompasses parts
of Brazoria, Fort Bend and Harris counties.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
