<P>
   (NYT16) CEDARHURST, N.Y. -- Sept. 15, 1999 -- NY-ORTHODOX-LIFE,
09-15 --Two Orthodox Jewish women, dressed to cover their elbows
and knees in accordance with Orthodox Jewish tradition, push their
strollers past a Victoria's Secret store on Central Avenue earlier
this week. Cedarhurst and the other Five Towns on Long Island have
been a citadel of Jewish suburbia for generations and a stronghold
of Orthodoxy for more than a decade. But the new wave of young
families are inventing a new style of Jewish life that is one part
Orthodox Judaism and one part quintessential suburbia. (James
Estrin/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT16) CEDARHURST, N.Y. -- Sept. 15, 1999 -- NY-ORTHODOX-LIFE,
