<P>
   (NYT15) GREAT BARRINGTON, Mass. -- Sept. 15, 1999 --
SHEEP-FARMER-BOS, 09-15 -- Lila Berle walks with her sheep on the
across the defunct dairy farm she bought so she could raise sheep
and bale her own hay. ``I'm having a ball,'' says Mrs. Berle, 62.
``I love the land and I love the animals.'' (Tom Herde/Boston Globe
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT14) PHILADELPHIA -- Sept. 15, 1999 -- CIR-MAPS, 09-15 -- At
Pennsylvania State University, a campus map prototype responds to
speech and gestures. Researchers in the university's computer
science and engineering department have been working for more than
two years to create the prototype, a map of the university's main
campus, in University Park, which projects an image of Penn State's
buildings and grounds onto a 60-inch television monitor. (New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
