The hurricane is expected to make landfall late tonight or early
Thursday somewhere along the North Carolina coast. From there, the
storm was expected to weaken but make life miserable all the way up
the coast toward Canada's New Brunswick. (James Estrin/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
