   (NYT8) DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. -- Sept. 15, 1999 --
HURRICANE-FLOYD-3, 09-15 -- Residents look at what is left of the
Main Street Pier on Daytona Beach after a 100-feet section was
washed away by powerful waves from Hurricane Floyd on Wednesday.
Although the hurricane stayed off Florida's Atlantic coast during
the night, parts of the state were raked by strong gusts. (Timothy
O. Davis/The Gainesville Sun)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) WRIGHTSVILLE BEACH, N.C. -- Sept. 15, 1999 --
