<SLUG> BC-CHURCHSHOOTING-1stLdWritethru-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SEVEN REPORTED KILLED AT FORT WORTH CHURCH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ A gunman walked into a sanctuary full of
young people at a southwest Fort Worth Baptist church Wednesday
evening and began firing, killing seven, including himself,
officials said. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The shooting occurred at the Wedgwood Baptist Church about 7
p.m. during a rally related to ``See You at The Pole,'' which
attracted hundreds of teen-agers from several area churches. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   When the gunman entered the church, a number of teens thought it
was a skit, witnesses said. But members of Forty Days, the band
playing at the event, reportedly started ducking behind
amplifiers. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Initial reports also indicated that a pipe bomb might have
exploded, sending shrapnel all the way into the balcony. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``There's cartridges, shrapnel and empty cart boxes and blood
splattered all over the wall,'' said Lt. David Ellis, a police
spokesman at the scene. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The gunman was wearing a black leather jacket, bluejeans and a
bandanna when he walked into the church. A number of church members
said they did not recognize the man. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   An off-duty police officer who lives near the church heard the
shots and called 911. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   One man was reportedly taken into custody for questioning, but
police did not say why. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Kristen Dickens, 14, said she was sitting in the second pew in
the sanctuary when the gunman entered through the rear. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``We had just finished singing and we were praying when he came
in,'' Dickens said. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   As many as 400 people may have been in the sanctuary, witnesses
said. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``We thought it was a joke,'' Dickens said. ``We were singing,
and he told us to shut up.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The gunman then began shooting in different directions. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought it was our pastor playing a joke on us. But then
Cassie got hit in the throat. She never got up,'' Dickens said. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-15-99 2143EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
