<HEADER>
A3670 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s BC-FBN-FALCONS-NOTES16-C     09-15 0606
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-FALCONS-NOTES16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Chandler between `doubtful and out'
 &HT;    By Matt Winkeljohn
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The sight of Falcons quarterback Chris Chandler
jogging Wednesday while teammates practiced 100 yards away was not
enough to buoy the spirits of coach Dan Reeves.
</P>
<P>
   Coaches were walking as fast as Chandler was jogging three days
after aggravating a previously strained right hamstring in a 17-14
loss to the Vikings.
</P>
<P>
   He may be a spectator Monday at Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think he would be ready to go,'' said Reeves, who gave
most of the work with the No. 1 offense to backup quarterback Tony
Graziani. ``I would say he's extremely doubtful. He's between
doubtful and out.''
</P>
<P>
   Chandler sounded only a little more optimistic.
</P>
<P>
   Other aches and pains
</P>
<P>
   Wide receiver Tim Dwight (strained right hamstring) also missed
Wednesday's light practice, and like Chandler is listed as doubtful
on the injury report. ... Reserve cornerback Michael Booker
returned for the first time since aggravating a strained thigh
muscle Aug. 27. He ended up doing little. ``I'm not where I want to
be,'' he said. ... Defensive tackle Ben Huff, who had been out
since Aug. 27 with a sprained foot, also returned. ... The Cowboys'
injury report: Tight end Mike Lucky (foot) and cornerback Kevin
Smith (back), out; cornerback Deion Sanders (toe), doubtful; tight
end David LaFleur (ankle), wide receiver Jeff Ogden (thigh), and
strong safety Darren Woodson (biceps), probable. Sanders, the
former Falcon sidelined all but a couple of days after surgery to
correct ligament damage in a big toe, may practice today.
</P>
<P>
   Big numbers
</P>
<P>
   Defensive tackle Travis Hall's four-year extension gives him a
seven-year deal worth $52.5 million, more than any contract in team
history.
</P>
<P>
   But as with all big NFL contracts, the numbers need
interpretation.
</P>
<P>
   Including Hall's $5.1 million signing bonus, it's likely to end
up a four-year, $16.5 million, or three-year, $10.5 million deal.
</P>
<P>
   Jamal Anderson's five-year, $32 million deal, which had a $7.5
million bonus, can be broken down into a four-year, $21.3 million
deal, or a three-year, $15.3 million deal
</P>
<P>
   All big NFL contracts have breakoff points, where they're likely
to be terminated or re-worked because the annual salary-cap charges
get so high.
</P>
<P>
   Hall's cap charges in 2002, '03, '04, and '05 are scheduled at
$6.7 million, $10.7 million, $12.7 million and $14.7 million.
</P>
<P>
   Planning ahead
</P>
<P>
   Among the seven Falcons starters who can become unrestricted
free agents after this season, talks are most active with left
defensive end Lester Archambeau and center Robbie Tobeck, and also
reserve linebacker Craig Sauer.
</P>
<P>
   There is little going on regarding extensions for tight end O.J.
Santiago or strong-side linebacker Henri Crockett, who can become
restricted free agents.
</P>
<P>
   Extra points
</P>
<P>
   The Falcons signed defensive end Emil Ekiyor to the practice
squad. He replaces wide receiver Jammi German, who was activated
Tuesday, when defensive tackle Shawn Swayda was waived. ... There
were huge speakers on either side of the practice field Wednesday,
as the team prepared for anticipated crowd noise. ... While Atlanta
will have just five days after the Monday night game to prepare for
its next game, the Falcons' Sept. 26 opponent will have two weeks.
The Rams (1-0) are off this week. ... An example of how numbers can
obfuscate: The Falcons are 0-4 in games Calvin Collins doesn't
start at left guard or center, and 23-9 in games he does.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
