<SLUG> BC-KIDS:FACES:EMILY-HART-CLASSACTS-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FACES: MEET EMILY HART 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By JESSAMY BROWN 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Meet: Emily Hart, little sister of Melissa Joan Hart.
</P>
<P>
   Claim to fame: Stars in ``Sabrina, the Animated Series.''
</P>
<P>
   Age/grade: 13; eighth grade.
</P>
<P>
   Hobbies: Basketball, spending time with friends.
</P>
<P>
   Career plans: Marine biology.
</P>
<P>
   Favorite subjects: math, French, science.
</P>
<P>
   Another ``Sabrina, the Teenage Witch'' TV show. Another Hart as
the star.
</P>
<P>
   Emily Hart is the voice of half-mortal, half-witch Sabrina in a
new animated spinoff of the prime-time show that stars her older
sister, Melissa Joan Hart.
</P>
<P>
   The new show, which will run Sunday through Friday afternoons on
UPN and on Saturday mornings on ABC, is a prequel to the sitcom,
and centers on the mishaps of Sabrina Spellman at age 12 _ before
she has full access to her powers and spells.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sabrina's got the same attitude, but she's kind of just
finding out who she is,'' Emily said in a telephone interview.
</P>
<P>
   Melissa, 23, is in the animated show, too. She lends her voice
to two characters, aunts Hilda Spellman and Zelda Spellman. In this
prequel, they are both centuries-old witches who have taken on
mortal form as teen-agers.
</P>
<P>
   Emily, who got her acting start at 9 months in a commercial, has
recorded 65 episodes. Emily does her part while alone in a studio,
so technically, she's not working with her sister.
</P>
<P>
   ``I went in after school and I acted out two scripts per
session. When I go into the studio, it takes about an hour and a
half so it doesn't really interfere with school,'' Emily said,
adding that she doesn't see the animated action while she records.
``I kind of imagine it in my head because they match the animation
to my voice.''
</P>
<P>
   Emily is serious about a career in marine biology and is
decorating her room with posters of whales, dolphins and seals.
It's a big deal, Emily says, because she just got her own room
thanks to two sisters who went off to college, and Melissa, who
recently moved into her own house.
</P>
<P>
   Emily is the fifth child in a family of eight kids. The
children, seven sisters and one brother, have all done some acting,
she added.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
