BOOK REVIEW: ``BILL NYE THE SCIENCE GUY'S BIG BLUE OCEAN'' 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 By SEAN SEAVER, (High School) Student Reporter 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOOK: ``Bill Nye the Science Guy's Big Blue Ocean''
</P>
<P>
   Authors: Bill Nye and Ian G. Saunders.
</P>
<P>
   Illustrator: John S. Dykes.
</P>
<P>
   Price: $15.99 hardcover.
</P>
<P>
   Ages: 7-10.
</P>
<P>
   Publisher: Hyperion Books for Children.
</P>
<P>
   This is a short (48 pages) educational book about Earth's oceans
and the creatures that live in them. It has 12 fun experiments to
do at home.
</P>
<P>
   This book has almost 50 colorfully illustrated pages of ocean
facts and cool experiments like how to make a tsunami, also called
a tidal wave, in your bathtub, or how to eat like a whale.
</P>
<P>
   The host of the PBS TV show guides readers through each of the
neat experiments, step by step.
</P>
<P>
   I thought this was a really interesting book, and I learned a
lot. This would be a great book to have in a classroom for both the
teacher and the students.
</P>
<P>
   Reviewer's 1 - 10 rating: 9.
