<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Terms in the wrestling world: Blading
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Act of a wrestler cutting himself with a sharp object,
usually a part of a razor blade, in order to bleed. The act is
usually done when the wrestler is face down and moves his hands to
his forehead. The wrestler will pull the blade from his trunks or
wrist band and open the cut. Former wrestlers like Dusty Rhodes and
Wahoo McDaniel did it so much that they developed scar tissue on
their foreheads.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
